class:: PassiveLPFCh
summary:: Passive second-order RC low-pass filter port from WaveDigitalFilters
categories:: UGens>Filters
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

PassiveLPFCh follows the `PassiveLPF` example from `WaveDigitalFilters`. The circuit is a passive second-order RC low-pass network evaluated through a 2x oversampled wave-digital shell, so the cutoff behavior is produced by the same resistor-capacitor energy exchange as the analog prototype rather than by a generic biquad coefficient formula. Because the network is passive, the filter naturally trades brightness for level as the cutoff moves downward.

In practice this reads as a straightforward but musical tone roll-off. It is useful when you want filtering that feels like simple analog loading and attenuation rather than a resonant or overtly synthetic filter gesture.

classmethods::

method::ar

argument::in
Input signal.

argument::freq
Cutoff frequency in Hz. Clamped to `20..20000`.

argument::mul
Output multiplier.

argument::add
Output offset.


